subSection.paragraph:
The possible preference for the calls of certain frog species seems to be a relevant factor that influences the diversity of frog-biting midges captured (
Ambrozio-Assis et al. 2019
). In our study, it was not possible to evaluate the preference of species of
Corethrella
to a specific type of frog call, because we used a database with more than 80 frog sounds. Most of the individuals were collected in the modified trap, with speakers; similar results were also found in studies of
Caldart et al. (2016)
. Some other studies carried out in Brazil ( Amaral & Pinho 2015 ;
Amaral et al. 2019
;
Caldart et al. 2016
), using same collection methods, captured less samples. Partly, this can be explained by the differences in collection methods, frog and toad mosquito fauna, and biomes.
